description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/routing/dtn.c
Lines: 64-81

In evict_if_needed():

    while (buf->current_bytes + new_size > buf->max_bytes) {
        int oldest = find_oldest(buf);
        if (oldest < 0) {
            break;
        }
        buf->current_bytes -= message_size(&buf->messages[oldest]);
        buf->messages[oldest].valid = false;
        buf->count--;
        evicted++;
    }

Scenario for unbounded loop:
1. max_bytes = 1000
2. Message A: packet_len=400, message_size=500
3. Message B: packet_len=400, message_size=500  
4. current_bytes = 1000 (A+B)
5. Try to add Message C with new_size=600

Loop iteration:
- Evict A: current_bytes=500, still 500+600=1100 > 1000
- Evict B: current_bytes=0, now 0+600=600 <= 1000, loop exits

This works, but if new_size > max_bytes (which is checked earlier), we'd evict everything and still fail.

Actually the check at line 125-126 prevents new_size > max_bytes, so this is protected. Downgrading to note that the protection is important.
